# Python Standards

## Version
- 3.11+ for applications
- 3.9+ for published libraries

## Dependencies
- Minimal, pinned versions in pyproject.toml
- Use `uv` for package management
- No separate requirements.txt — pyproject.toml is the single source

## Validation
- Pydantic for data boundaries (configs, API inputs, external data)
- Type hints on all public APIs
- dataclasses for internal-only structured data

## Testing
- pytest with pytest-cov
- 80%+ coverage on core logic
- Fixtures in conftest.py
- Mark slow tests: @pytest.mark.slow

## Style
- Linting: `ruff check .`
- Formatting: `ruff format .`
- Type checking: `ty check src/`
- Line length: 100

## Structure
```
src/<package_name>/
    __init__.py
    ...
tests/
    conftest.py
    test_*.py
pyproject.toml
```

## CI
- `ruff check .`
- `ruff format --check .`
- `ty check src/`
- `pytest --cov`
